# Dev integration branch

**`dev`** is the required intermediary between task branches and **`main`**.

```
task branch → dev (CI / early prod) → main (stable release)
```

## Pull requests

- **Always** open feature/fix PRs with base **`dev`**, not `main`.
- Use `gh pr create --base dev` (or retarget with `gh pr edit <n> --base dev`).
- PRs to **`main`** are only for promoting **`dev`** (release/integration) or when the user explicitly requests a hotfix directly to `main`.

## Branching

- Create task branches from an up-to-date **`dev`**: `git fetch origin && git checkout dev && git pull origin dev --ff-only`, then `git checkout -b feature/...`.
- Before `git worktree add`, sync **`dev`** the same way (not `main`) unless the user specifies another base.

## Keeping dev current

- When **`main`** moves ahead (release, hotfix), fast-forward or merge **`main`** into **`dev`** so the integration branch does not drift.
- Do not force-push **`dev`** without the user’s OK.

## CI / deploy

- Point preview/staging CI at **`dev`** so merged features ship early before **`main`** promotion.

## Linear alignment

- When a PR exists targeting **`dev`**, Linear issue status **Needs Review** still applies per `.cursor/rules/linear-github-pr-status.mdc`.
